          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "VitaFreshPro (also marketed as 'Freshness Keeper' on some model years) is Bosch's humidity-controlled produce drawer system in 800 Series and Benchmark refrigerators. Two drawers with independent humidity sensors and electric humidity control — high humidity for leafy greens and vegetables, low humidity for fruits. When produce doesn't last as advertised, three causes: (1) humidity sensor drifted, reading incorrectly and setting wrong humidity levels — $125-$185 sensor replacement; (2) drawer seal damaged or debris preventing proper seal closure, humidity escapes — free fix with cleaning or $85-$145 seal replacement; (3) user configuration mismatch — produce in the wrong-humidity drawer (this is surprisingly common, free diagnostic to identify). We verify sensor calibration and seal integrity during any VitaFreshPro service call."
        }
